title.narrative: 5.3 SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: 5.3 Social Assistance coverage and quality is extended and strengthened through direct provision as well as through leading the technical expertise, evidence, analysis and advocacy needed to develop Lebanon's National Social Protection System, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Evaluation, Research, Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 5. By the end of 2022, multidimensional child poverty in Lebanon is reduced with increased national and community level action for children

title.narrative: 5.3 Social Assistance coverage and quality is extended and strengthened through direct provision as well as through leading thetechnical expertise, evidence, analysis and advocacy needed to develop Lebanon's National Social Protection System

description.narrative: UNICEF Lebanon&39;s work on social protection in 2021 was characterized by key achievements including the completion of the National Social Protection Strategy, as well as extensive, successful advocacy to develop the national social assistance system and introduce national social grants that address life-cycle vulnerabilities. Furthermore, UNICEF’s delivery of social assistance significantly increased with the launch of the Haddi child grant, a large-scale cash plus programme, as well as initiating design of a National Disability Allowance for launch in early 2022. | Status:Met | As-of Date:09/12/2021
